al to smoke on any French beaches.\", \"from\": 917, \"to\": 981, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 966, \"end\": 972, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/French_language\", \"score\": 0.9301716348022413, \"rank\": 0.07506965361022115, \"text\": \"French\", \"types\": [\"Q315\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/French_language\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/French_language\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"this year\", \"from\": 922, \"to\": 931}]}, {\"sentence\": \"So much foregalite.\", \"from\": 983, \"to\": 1002, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"So much foregalite\", \"from\": 983, \"to\": 1001}]}, {\"sentence\": \"These examples of French bureaucracy are \\\"de rigueur\\\" for the country that wrote the rulebook picked up by much of the world.\", \"from\": 1004, \"to\": 1129, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1022, \"end\": 1028, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/French_language\", \"score\": 0.9301716348022413, \"rank\": 0.07506965361022115, \"text\": \"French\", \"types\": [\"Q315\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/French_language\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/French_language\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"These examples\", \"from\": 1004, \"to\": 1018}, {\"ngram\": \"the country\", \"from\": 1062, \"to\": 1073}, {\"ngram\": \"the rulebook\", \"from\": 1085, \"to\": 1097}, {\"ngram\": \"the world\", \"from\": 1119, \"to\": 1128}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Since the introduction of the Code Napoleon 220 years ago, there have been some interesting rules and bylaws that seem purposely designed to bamboozle tourists.\", \"from\": 1131, \"to\": 1291, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"the introduction\", \"from\": 1137, \"to\": 1153}, {\"ngram\": \"the Code Napoleon\", \"from\": 1157, \"to\": 1174}, {\"ngram\": \"some interesting rules\", \"from\": 1206, \"to\": 1228}, {\"ngram\": \"bylaws\", \"from\": 1233, \"to\": 1239}, {\"ngram\": \"tourists\", \"from\": 1282, \"to\": 1290}]}