oughout the journey.\", \"from\": 1897, \"to\": 2006, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"Animals\", \"from\": 1897, \"to\": 1904}, {\"ngram\": \"kg\", \"from\": 1912, \"to\": 1914}, {\"ngram\": \"a container\", \"from\": 1938, \"to\": 1949}, {\"ngram\": \"larger pets\", \"from\": 1955, \"to\": 1966}, {\"ngram\": \"the journey\", \"from\": 1994, \"to\": 2005}]}, {\"sentence\": \"The cost of a \\\"large\\\" pet fare is set at 50 per cent of a second-class ticket.\", \"from\": 2007, \"to\": 2085, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"The cost\", \"from\": 2007, \"to\": 2015}, {\"ngram\": \"a \\\"large\\\" pet fare\", \"from\": 2019, \"to\": 2037}, {\"ngram\": \"50 per cent\", \"from\": 2048, \"to\": 2059}, {\"ngram\": \"a second-class ticket\", \"from\": 2063, \"to\": 2084}]}, {\"sentence\": \"It's one of France's most cliched holiday snaps.It is also illegal after dark.\", \"from\": 2087, \"to\": 2165, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 2099, \"end\": 2105, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/France\", \"score\": 0.9999999999990905, \"rank\": 9.525009420652094e-13, \"text\": \"France\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/France\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/France\"}], \"noun_phrases\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"This is not because there are too many of them, but because the picture is patented intellectual property.\", \"from\": 2167, \"to\": 2273, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"the picture\", \"from\": 2227, \"to\": 2238}, {\"ngram\": \"patented intellectual property\", \"from\": 2242, \"to\": 2272}]}, {\"sentence\": \"While the tower's image passed into public domain in 1993, 70 years after the death of architect Gustav Eiffel, the light display was switched on in only 1985.\", \"from\": 2275, \"to\": 2434, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 2372, \"end\": 2385, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Gustave_Eiffel\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Gustav Eiffel\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Gustave_Eiffel\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Gustave_Eiffel\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"the tower's image\", \"from\": 2281, \"to\": 2298}, {\"ngram\": \"public domain\", \"from\": 2311, \"to\": 2324}, {\"ngram\": \"the death\", \"from\": 2349, \"to\": 2358}, {\"ngram\": \"the light display\", \"from\": 2387, \"to\": 2404}]}, {\"sentence\": \"The Societe d'Exploitation de la Tour Eiffel can stop professional photographers from profiting from the illuminations.\", \"from\": 2436, \"to\": 2555, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 2466, \"end\": 2480, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/La_Tour_Eiffel_(Hopi_Hari)\", \"score\": 0.9999999995834514, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"la Tour Eiffel\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/La_Tour_Eiffel_(Hopi_Hari)\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/La_Tour_Eiffel_(Hopi_Hari)\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"professional photographers\", \"from\": 2490, \"to\": 2516}, {\"ngram\": \"the illuminations\", \"from\": 2537, \"to\": 2554}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Though it is thought to be largely unenforceable, in theory, anyone taking pictures of the 20,000 twinkly lights between nightfall and 1am risks breaking French copyright law.\", \"from\": 2557, \"to\": 2732, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 2711, \"end\": 2731, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Copyright_law_of_France\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"French copyright law\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Copyright_law_of_France\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Copyright_law_of_France\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"theory\", \"from\": 2610, \"to\": 2616}, {\"ngram\": \"anyone\", \"from\": 2618, \"to\": 2624}, {\"ngram\": \"pictures\", \"from\": 2632, \"to\": 2640}, {\"ngram\": \"the 20,000 twinkly lights\", \"from\": 2644, \"to\": 2669}, {\"ngram\": \"nightfall\", \"from\": 2678, \"to\": 2687}, {\"ngram\": \"risks\", \"from\": 2696, \"to\": 2701}]}, {\"sentence\": \"\\u2026 or at least it is if you leave the curtains open.\", \"from\": 2734, \"to\": 2785, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"the curtains\", \"from\": 2767, \"to\": 2779}]}, {\"sentence\": \"You could be fined \\u20ac15,000-30,000 ($27,000-$54,000) if you are found to be visible \\\"au naturel\\\" even in the confines of your hotel room or private residence.\", \"from\": 2787, \"to\": 2944, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"au naturel\", \"from\": 2871, \"to\": 2881}, {\"ngram\": \"the confines\", \"from\": 2891, \"to\": 2903}, {\"ngram\": \"your hotel room\", \"from\": 2907, \"to\": 2922}, {\"ngram\": \"private residence\", \"from\": 2926, \"to\": 2943}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Despite France's reputation for a laissez-faire attitude towards nudity, there are some strict laws around when and where you can be sans clothes.\", \"from\": 2946, \"to\": 3092, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 2954, \"end\": 2960, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/France\", \"score\": 0.9999999999990905, \"rank\": 9.525009420652094e-13, \"text\": \"France\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/France\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/France\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"a laissez-faire attitude\", \"from\": 2978, \"to\": 3002}, {\"ngram\": \"nudity\", \"from\": 3011, \"to\": 3017}, {\"ngram\": \"some strict laws\", \"from\": 3029, \"to\": 3045}, {\"ngram\": \"sans clothes\", \"from\": 3079, \"to\": 3091}]}, {\"sentence\": \"The law is designed to avoid sexual exhibitionism and prevents people from being visibly naked in public, even if you are on private property.\", \"from\": 3093, \"to\": 3235, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"The law\", \"from\": 3093, \"to\": 3100}, {\"ngram\": \"sexual exhibitionism\", \"from\": 3122, \"to\": 3142}, {\"ngram\": \"people\", \"from\": 3156, \"to\": 3162}, {\"ngram\": \"private property\", \"from\": 3218, \"to\": 3234}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Be careful where you choose to get dressed.\", \"from\": 3236, \"to\": 3279, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Despite this, nudist beaches maintain popularity with some visitors.\", \"from\": 3281, \"to\": 3349, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"nudist beaches\", \"from\": 3295, \"to\": 3309}, {\"ngram\": \"popularity\", \"from\": 3319, \"to\": 3329}, {\"ngram\": \"some visitors\", \"from\": 3335, \"to\": 3348}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Although, according tothelocal.fr, under French law even visitors to a plage de nudistes can be charged with \\\"disturbing the peace\\\" if someone takes exception to their state of undress.\", \"from\": 3350, \"to\": 3535, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 3391, \"end\": 3401, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/France\", \"score\": 0.9999330672790256, \"rank\": 6.693539997845763e-05, \"text\": \"French law\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/France\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/France\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"tothelocal.fr\", \"from\": 3370, \"to\": 3383}, {\"ngram\": \"a plage de nudistes\", \"from\": 3419, \"to\": 3438}, {\"ngram\": \"the peace\", \"from\": 3471, \"to\": 3480}, {\"ngram\": \"someone\", \"from\": 3485, \"to\": 3492}, {\"ngram\": \"exception\", \"from\": 3499, \"to\": 3508}, {\"ngram\": \"their state\", \"from\": 3512, \"to\": 3523}, {\"ngram\": \"undress\", \"from\": 3527, \"to\": 3534}]}, {\"sentence\": \"The croissant and \\\"le dejeuner\\\" are sacrosanct.\", \"from\": 3537, \"to\": 3584, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"\\\"le dejeuner\", \"from\": 3555, \"to\": 3567}]}, {\"sentence\": \"There are several laws to protect local cafes and employees' rights to enjoy a pause for kai, but also for the establishments serving them.\", \"from\": 3586, \"to\": 3725, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"several laws\", \"from\"